text: Clavaria versatilis is a species of coral fungus in the family Clavariaceae. It was first described scientifically by French mycologist Lucien Quélet in 1893 as a species of Ramaria. Pier Andrea Saccardo and Alessandro Trotter transferred it to the genus Clavaria in 1912. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Clavariaceae Category:Fungi described in 1893 Category:Fungi of Australia
